<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">CARAMELIZED ONIONS, MUSHROOMS, AND BACON</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page065.article001.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY SARAH SWIHART</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 15 to 20 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 (16-ounce) package bacon, chopped </p><p class="no-indent">2 (8-ounce) packages sliced baby portobello mushrooms </p><p class="no-indent">10 large sweet onions, thinly sliced </p><p class="no-indent">1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon ground black pepper </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. In a large Dutch oven, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Using a slotted spoon, remove bacon from pan, and drain on paper towels, leaving ¼ cup drippings in pan. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. Cook mushrooms in hot drippings over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until very tender. Using a slotted spoon, remove mushrooms from pan, and drain on paper towels. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Add onions to hot drippings. Cover, and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes, or until onions are very tender. Increase heat to medium-high. Cook, stirring constantly, until onions caramelize or begin to turn golden brown. Stir in vinegar, pepper, bacon, and mushrooms.</p></div>
